== Gloria Patri == 

'''Gloria Patri''', also known as the '''Glory Be to the Father''' or, colloquially, the '''Glory Be''', is a [[doxology]], a short [[hymn]] of praise to [[God]] in various [[Kristanvponn|Christian]] [[liturgy|liturgies]]. It is also referred to as the ''Minor Doxology (Doxologia Minor)'' or ''Lesser Doxology'', to distinguish it from the ''Greater Doxology'', the [[Gloria in Excelsis Deo]].

==Roman Rite Latin version==


:Gloria Patri, et Filio, et Spiritui Sancto,
:Sicut erat in principio, et nunc, et semper, et in saecula saeculorum. Amen.


== English Version == 

:Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit,
:As it was in the beginning, both now, and always, and to ages of ages. Amen.


